                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240603-110-victim946 t18240603-110-viclabel580"></join>; I was at work in Gloucester-street, Hoxton, building a new house; I left the saws there at twelve o'clock on the 6th of May, and had seen the prisoner near the house; I put a piece of wood against the door when I went away; I returned at one o'clock, and they were gone.</p>

